						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up near the northern gateway leading to the Tuṅgabhadrā river in the Paṁpāpāti temple.</p>						

						<p>Harihara II, 1379 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This damaged record, in Sanskrit and Kannaḍa, is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1301</hi> (expressed in the chronogram <hi rend="italic">Śaśi-khē-śikhibhēndra</hi>), <hi rend="bold">Siddhārti, Jyēshṭha, Tuesday,</hi> lunar eclipse corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1379 A.D., May 31.</hi></p>						

						<p>It registers the gift of land to the temple of Virūpākshadēva, by Mudda-daṇḍēśa, at the instance of the king. </p>						

						</summary>
